com.ericramirezs.commando4j.command.arguments

Class UnionArgument

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ericramirezs.commando4j.command.arguments.Argument<UnionArgument,IArgument>
      • com.ericramirezs.commando4j.command.arguments.UnionArgument
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IArgument<UnionArgument,IArgument>

    public final class UnionArgument
extends Argument<UnionArgument,IArgument>
    A type for command arguments that handles multiple other types.

    It will try to parse arguments in the same order they're added. The first success will be the Value of this argument.

    Make sure to use instanceof to check what of Argument was the valid one.

      • clone

        public UnionArgument clone()
        Description copied from class: Argument
        An argument clone is required to prevent a value traveling through different Command calls.

        If your Argument child doesn't have additional attribute, you may just do return clone(new MyArgument(getName(), getPrompt()));
